Akamaihd.net is a content delivery platform used by some of the biggest tech companies in the world to stream audio and video and host downloads¹. It's not a virus or any other form of malware¹. However, there are browser hijackers whose distributors use Akamai hosting, which means that their URLs have “Akamaihd.net” in them¹. If you are attacked by a browser hijacker, you may notice redirects to an Akamaihd.net address².
